description:
Keep the selection cursor visible in the task list even when focus is on another pane.

## Current Behavior

When user presses Tab to move focus to details/output pane, the highlight/cursor on the selected task in the task list disappears.

## Desired Behavior

- Cursor remains visible but with different styling (e.g., dimmed, different color, or outline instead of filled)
- Focused pane has bright/active cursor style
- Unfocused pane has dim/inactive cursor style

## Implementation

### internal/tui/model.go

In task list rendering, check if pane is focused:

```go
func (m *Model) renderTaskLine(task TaskInfo, selected bool, width int) string {
    if selected {
        if m.focusedPane == PaneTaskList {
            // Active selection - bright highlight
            return activeSelectedStyle.Render(line)
        } else {
            // Inactive selection - dimmed highlight  
            return inactiveSelectedStyle.Render(line)
        }
    }
    // ...
}
```

## Nice to Have

This is lower priority - implement if straightforward, skip if complex.
